---
title: Garlicky Shrimp Couscous Bowls with Chili-Roasted Broccoli & Fresh Parsley
description: Bowls are a go-to meal when we’re in the mood for creative lunch and dinner ideas. Why? It’s simple: everything’s better in a bowl! This quick, fresh rendition is a great way to meet your summer goals (including getting back outside more quickly!). You’ll top garlic, lemon, and parsley-scented Israeli couscous with quick-cooking garlicky shrimp, chili-roasted broccoli, and a rich drizzle of delicious lemon-butter sauce. One bite = totally bowled over.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/garlicky-shrimp-couscous-bowls-518874cd.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/garlicky-shrimp-couscous-bowls-6447d2af33e34d0ea5018115-29030d7b.pdf
time required: 25 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 490 kcal
  fat: 20 g
  saturated fat: 5 g
  carbohydrates: 45 g
  sugar: 5 g
  protein: 26 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1030 mg
servings: 2
author: Sara Heilman
cuisine: Italian
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/garlicky-shrimp-couscous-bowls-6447d2af33e34d0ea5018115
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}. Finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{}, @chili flakes{1/2%tsp} (use less if you prefer less heat), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> Use 3/4 tsp chili flakes for 4 servings.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the garlic; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While couscous cooks, rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water; pat dry with paper towels. Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add shrimp, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper. Cook until shrimp are pink and almost cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add @water{2%TBSP}; cook, stirring and scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan, until water has evaporated, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Reduce heat to medium; add @butter{1%tbsp}, remaining garlic, and a pinch of chili flakes. Cook, stirring, until shrimp are cooked through and garlic is fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Remove pan from heat; toss shrimp with half the parsley and juice from half the lemon.

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}; stir in remaining parsley, a squeeze of lemon juice, and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide couscous between #bowls{}. Top with shrimp and broccoli. Spoon any remaining garlic butter from pan over shrimp. Serve with a squeeze of lemon juice.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.